text: Cation diffusion through compacted clays is of great interest due to its potential for buffer materials for waste disposal.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Cation Diffusion in Compacted Clay: A Pore-Scale View
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: It is indicated that the normalized volume charge density has a significant impact on the cationic diffusion.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: However, once an ion strength gradient is added, the electromigration process should be considered carefully due to its non-negligible role to balance the alteration of total flux.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: The present study could help improve the understanding of the transport mechanism of simple cationic tracers in compacted clays.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The importance of the electrokinetic effect on cationic tracer diffusion is investigated by using pore-scale simulations to consider the influence from the electrokinetic properties and topology of clays.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: For many cations at low concentrations, it has been reported that the cations diffuse through compacted clay at a greater rate than neutral or negatively charged species.1 The concept of “surface diffusion” is often employed to explain the large flux of cations compared with neutral species from experimental measurements.2 It is usually attributed to the interaction of cations with negatively charged surfaces of clays, and this electrostatic interaction increases the flux along surfaces within the electrical double layer (EDL) referred to the surface diffusion.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: However, the existence and importance of surface diffusion for different cations in various compacted clays is still doubtful.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: It was reported that the surface diffusion was unimportant for Cs+ in dense clays3 or FEBEX bentonite4 and not important for Sr2+ and Na+ in compacted clays.5
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: Instead, a lot of measurements showed that the surface diffusion was important for Cs+ and Na+ in compacted montmorillonite1 or important for Na+, Sr2+, and Zn2+ in compacted illite.6,7 Moreover, the importance of surface diffusion through clay-based materials also depends on ion salinity, pH, clay density, and clay composition.1,5,6
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: Recently, several continuum-scale models have been developed to describe sorbed cation diffusion through compacted clays, such as the models based on the Donnan theory,8−11 or the models that may include separated bulk diffusion, surface diffusion, and interlayer diffusion.2,12,13
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Admittedly, these phenomenological formulas could enhance the understanding and explain some experimental results, but parameters involved in the generalized Fick’s law had to be determined empirically or by fitting with experiment data.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: For instance, the surface diffusion coefficient Ds of sorbed cations is often involved in these phenomenological formulas.14 However, the relative surface diffusion coefficient of the cesium ion depends on the tracer’s concentration ranging from 0.1 to 0.00012 by fitting with the experiment data.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: Besides, the sorption distribution coefficient KD is also uncertain.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Different methods (batch or diffusion experiment) give various KD values.15 To simplify the diffusion in three-dimensional microstructures of clays into the diffusion in a one-dimensional channel, the previous studies2,13,16 also assume that the tortuosity of sorbed cations’ diffusion is the same as that of neutral species’ diffusion.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: This assumption may be reasonable for the interlayer pores in compacted montmorillonite, but for illite or kaolinite without interlayer pores, it may be different due to the rough surfaces of clay particles.17 In particular, when the pore size is at nanoscale or the clay density is high, the experimental study becomes time-consuming and difficult.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Besides, the assumptions and the physical meanings of parameters (e.g., Ds) in the generalized Fick’s law are uncertain for different species and clay minerals.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_SUPPLEMENT

text: factors.2,14,18 Our goals are (1) to reveal the mechanism of surface diffusion for simple positively charged tracers (like sodium ions) in compacted clays under a constant ion strength or under an ion strength gradient and (2) to quantitatively investigate under what conditions the cationic surface diffusion is significant.

text: We deal with a technical issue of assembling a ring part into a shaft part with the clearance of several micrometers by using a robotic manipulator.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: This issue is difficult because of deformation of a ring part compared with peg-in-hole assembly.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: We propose a precise assembly method of a ring part with finger shape to solve this issue.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: We also propose a method to decide design parameters of the finger by maximizing a closed area in Jamming diagram, which represents a successful condition of assembling rigid parts by quasi-static force analysis.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Finally, availability of the proposed method is verified by an experiment of ring assembly with a robotic hand attached to the designed fingers.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In recent years, many manufacturing companies have adopted Factory Automation (FA).
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Introduction of FA brings automation of various production processes, which are conducted by human workers, by machines, and can improve productivity, manufacturing cost, and quality of products.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Although a paint process, a weld process and an inspection process have been automated increasingly, most of the assembly processes have been conducted manually by human workers even now.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: This is because assembly processes by a robot has many issues with regard to the precision and flexibility.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Assembly methods by a robot are divided into two categories by focusing on a process of mating: a passive assembly method and an active assembly method.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The passive assembly method is a method that adjusts position and orientation of a part automatically by using mechanical elastic elements or guiding jig.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The passive assembly has advantage of high speed assembly because of sensor-less.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: However, the method is applied for only simple parts.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: In contrast, the active assembly method is a method that controls impedance of an end effector properly with
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Passive assembly methods have been studied since the 1980s.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: As a representative research of a passive assembly method, Whitney proposed Jamming diagram, which represents a successful condition in peg-in-hole task [1].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: As a concrete example of passive assembly method, Remote Center Compliance (RCC) device has been also developed.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Moreover, many researches have been studied, and have extended application range of RCC devices [2–4].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Mouri et al dealt with narrow clearance assembly and solved problems of high friction and jamming by adding high-frequency vibration to a peg during insertion process [5].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: These conventional approaches have disadvantages: A mechanical element, such as a spring and a rubber, need frequent maintenance due to their degradation; the system tends to become large; the cost of design and production tends to become large.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Active assembly methods have been proposed much in recent years.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Many researches of force sensor feedback [6, 7] or vision sensor feedback have been studied.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Today, there are strong demand for assembly for flexible parts such as a cable and rubber.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: For example, Nakagaki et al.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Fukukawa et al Robomech J (2016) 3:16 tackled automatic insertions of linear and tubular flexible parts based on shape detection by vision sensor [8].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Even though many active assembly methods have been proposed, the methods that are used actually are few.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: One reason of this is difficulty of developing the system.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Another reason is adaptability.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Although human workers can detect and recover an error state of assembly quickly and succeed in the assembly smoothly, many assembly automation system cannot perform as well as human work.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In this paper, we focus on a precise ring assembly task as an example of difficult assembly.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: In the case of precise assembly that a clearance between a ring part and a shaft part is several micro meters, the assembly by a robotic manipulator is difficult.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: This is because a ring part deforms if the ring part is grasped by a robotic hand, and the clearance disappears.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: When practicability is considered, it is desired that such difficult assembly is realized at high speed with minimal sensor system.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: So far, the precise ring assembly task has been hanndled by a method using a jig which is one of passive methods.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The assembly processes are described in Fig.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Originally, the function of the jig is to adjust the position and orientation of the ring by guiding along with the incline when the robotic hand pushes the ring straight down.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In order to realize this guiding effect without using any jigs, we figured out a approach using a hollowed finger with an incline.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Our proposed hollowed finger also solves the problem of ring deformation due to hand grasping.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The finger design approach for realizing the handling an object including assembly have been studied long time.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Most pioneering research of gripper design was done by Mason [9].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: He formulated a planar pose problem and found a pushing plan to move a polygonal object to a specified goal position and orientation.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: This concept has become underlying of the self-alignment mechanism on sensor-less gripper.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Causey and Quinn summarized gripper design guidelines [10] and mentioned the importance of grasped part alignment as well as the importance of part deformation avoidance for increasing reliability.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Zhang and Goldberg proposed unique parallel-jaw grippers that can align an n-sided polygonal part in the vertical plane as the jaw close [11].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: They also proposed a numerical algorithm to design optimal gripper jaws [12].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Hirata et al proposed design of handling device for caging and aligning small circular objects [13].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: By designing the triangular finger tips, their hand can grasp a small object robustly at a unique position of the tips.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Although these conventional studies solve the problem of self-alignment of a part with gripper, the problem of alignment with other part is not considered.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: On the other hand, our proposed hollowed finger can align centers of a part and another part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The capability of self-alignment between two parts by using the hollowed finger is our original.

text: Ring assembly with hollowed finger Based on the successful conditions of ring assembly, this section proposes a precise assembly method of a ring with hollowed finger.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: A characteristic of the proposed method is to assemble a ring part into a shaft part with a hollow of each finger of a robotic hand.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The proposed method consists of three phases: approach, adjustment of axes, and mating and insertion.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Figure 5 shows an overview of the proposed method.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: In the first phase, the manipulator with having a ring part approaches a shaft part and release and hang on the ring part to the shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The disappearing of grip force restores circular shape of the ring from deformation.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In the second phase, the robotic hand goes down and holds a shaft part with covering the ring part in the hollows of fingers to adjust the axes of the robotic hand and the shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In the third phase, the robot goes down and the ring part is assembled successfully by an effect of a space of the hollow.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The proposed method has four advantages as follows.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Approach An objective of this step is rough positioning of a ring part to a shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Firstly, the robotic manipulator picks up a ring part from a feeder.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Then, the robotic manipulator approaches the shaft part and releases the ring part on the shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In this case of precise assembly of a ring part, the assembly cannot succeed because a clearance between a ring part and a shaft part disappears by deformation of the ring part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: On the other hand, if the positional difference between the ring part and the shaft part is large, the ring part falls from a shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Therefore, it is assumed that the robotic manipulator is controlled with possible accuracy.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Adjustment of axes One problem of assembly by a robotic manipulator is positional accuracy of the robot.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In general, six-axis manipulators have positional error of more than 20 μM. Precise assembly cannot succeed with only position control.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: An objective of this step is to reduce the positional and angular errors between the robotic hand and the shaft part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: A hand grasping motion makes the fingers move toward the hand center with same width.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: When the hand center is not aligned with the shaft center, a finger contacts with the shaft in first even though others do not.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The left figure in Fig.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The arm motion is generated based on Eq (9).

text: Mating and insertion An objective of this step is to achieve mating and inserting the ring part without jamming.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The robotic hand goes down in negative z direction along the shaft part.

text: Positional and angular errors between the ring part and the shaft part are reduced through the second phase.

text: Therefore, the ring part is assembled successfully without complicated control.

text: Advantages of the hollows on fingers are as follows: prevention of ring deformation, geometrical restriction of a ring part, giving optimal mating force to a ring part.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The first advantage is prevention of ring deformation.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: We show that the entropy of a message can be tested in a device-independent way.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Specifically, we consider a prepare-and-measure scenario with classical or quantum communication, and develop two different methods for placing lower bounds on the communication entropy, given observable data.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The first method is based on the framework of causal inference networks.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The second technique, based on convex optimization, shows that quantum communication provides an advantage over classical, in the sense of requiring a lower entropy to reproduce given data.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The development of device-independent (DI) quantum information processing has attracted growing attention recently.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The main idea behind this new paradigm is to achieve quantum information tasks, and guarantee their secure implementation, based on observed data alone.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Thus no assumption about the internal working of the devices used in the protocol is in principle required.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Notably, realistic protocols for DI quantum cryptography [1] and randomness generation [2, 3] were presented, with proof-of-concept experiments for the second [3, 4].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: The strong security of DI protocols finds its origin in a more fundamental aspect of physics, namely the fact that certain physical quantities admit a modelindependent description and can thus be certified in a DI way.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The most striking example is Bell nonlocality [5, 6], which can be certified (via Bell inequality violation) by observing strong correlations between the results of distant measurements.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Notably, this is possible in quantum theory, by performing well-chosen local measurements on distant entangled particles.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: More recently, it was shown that the dimension of an uncharacterized physical system (loosely speaking, the number of relevant degrees of freedom) can also be tested in a DI way [7–10].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Conceptually, this allows us to study quantum theory inside a larger framework of physical theories , which already brought insight to quantum foundations [11–14].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: From a more applied point of view, this allows for DI protocols and for black-box characterization of quantum systems [15–20].
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: In this context, it is natural to ask whether there exist other physical quantities which admit a DI characterization.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_OPEN_URL

text: Here we show that this is the case by demonstrating that the entropy of a message can be tested in a DI way.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Specifically, we present simple and efficient methods for placing lower bounds on the entropy of a classical (or quantum) communication based on observable data alone.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: We construct such “entropy witnesses” following two different approaches, first using the framework of causal inference networks [21], and

text: The first construction is very general, but usually gives suboptimal bounds.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: The second construction allows us to place tight bounds on the entropy of classical messages for given data.
label: DATA_AVAILABILITY_CLOSED

text: Moreover, it shows that quantum systems provide an advantage over classical ones, in the sense that they typically require lower entropy to reproduce a given set of data.
